{"word":"Mortar","slug":"mortar","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Mortar</b> 1. An instrument for pulverizing grains<br/> - General references<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=11&verse=8'>Num 11:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=20&chapter=27&verse=22'>Pro 27:22</a><br/><a href='S:Grinding'>Grinding</a>; <a href='S:Mill'>Mill</a> <br/> 2. A cement:<br/> - General references<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=2&chapter=1&verse=14'>Exo 1:14</a> <br/> - Slime used as, in building tower of Babel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=11&verse=3'>Gen 11:3</a> <br/> - Used to plaster houses<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=3&chapter=14&verse=42'>Lev 14:42</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=3&chapter=14&verse=45'>Lev 14:45</a> <br/> - Untempered, not enduring<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=26&chapter=13&verse=15'>Eze 13:15</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=26&chapter=22&verse=28'>Eze 22:28</a> <br/> - To be trodden to make firm<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=34&chapter=3&verse=14'>Nah 3:14</a> <br/> Figurative<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=23&chapter=41&verse=25'>Isa 41:25</a>"}]}